race.comment: BOOM CRUSHER (2) doesn't win out of turn but is usually thereabouts and saves his best form for his home circuit here. Racing consistently this time in work and is sure to run his usual honest race. SANTORINI SUMMER (4) has only missed a place once in ten starts over this course and distance and is drawn to get a cosy run from the inside alley. Top-three candidate. Former Victorian HUMBLE HERO (6) got the job done here first-up and can go right on with it now. Keep very safe. MR GREY (9) strips fitter second-up from the spell and can measure up on best figures. SHEEZA FLING (10) next in line on the back of a win here two back.
